  "original_title": "LPBOA appeals to youth, politicians, clergy, govt. servants to engage in betterment service",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "LPBOA appeals to youth, politicians, clergy, govt. servants to engage in betterment service",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Lanka Private Bus Owners' Association (LPBOA) today made several appeals to the youth who are engaged in Aragalaya, the politicians, government servants and the clergy who too are engaged to uphold the similar cause, to come out and serve for the benefit of the people of this country.",
        "LPBOA Chairman Gemunu Wijerathne staunchly appealed to the aragalaya youth that they should not be a cat's paw of anyone. He requested the politicians to stop the political games and bribing the people.",
        "Also he requested a few members of the clergy who are engaged in the Aragalaya to honour and respect the religious bodies they belong to.",
        "He also reiterated the government servants to be productive and unselfish when serving the country (Chaturanga Samarawickrama)"
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
          "text": "LPBOA",
          "label": "ORG"
        }
      ],
